Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
    int temperature;
    boolean isRainy;

    WeatherSimulator(int temp, boolean rain) {
        temperature = temp;
        isRainy = rain;
    }

    void updateWeather(int deltaTemp) {
        if (deltaTemp > 5) {
            temperature += deltaTemp;
            isRainy = true;
        } else {
            temperature += deltaTemp;
        }
    }

    void simulateDay() {
        if (temperature > 20) {
            System.out.println("Warm day");
        } else {
            System.out.println("Cool day");
        }
        if (isRainy) {
            System.out.println("Rainy day");
        }
    }
}",

Would setting 'isRainy' to true likely be a cause of the temperature being high?
